{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01342MaEBUMj2zwoX5m9mD8E","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"LLM agent context compression sliding window MemGPT 2025 baselines AgentGym\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"MemGPT\",\"url\":\"https://research.memgpt.ai/\"},{\"title\":\"Active Context Compression: Autonomous Memory Management in LLM Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2601.07190\"},{\"title\":\"Scaling LLM Multi-turn RL with End-to-end Summarization- ...\",\"url\":\"https://miaolu3.github.io/ArXiv_SUPO.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Acon: Optimizing Context Compression for Long-horizon LLM Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2510.00615v1\"},{\"title\":\"Preprint MEMGPT: TOWARDS LLMS AS OPERATING SYSTEMS Charles Packer Vivian Fang\",\"url\":\"https://readwise-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/media/wisereads/articles/memgpt-towards-llms-as-operati/MEMGPT.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"ACON: OPTIMIZING CONTEXT COMPRESSION FOR ...\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=7JbSwX6bNL\"},{\"title\":\"MemGPT: Towards LLMs as Operating Systems – Leonie Monigatti\",\"url\":\"https://www.leoniemonigatti.com/papers/memgpt.html\"},{\"title\":\"MemAgent: Reshaping Long-Context LLM with Multi-Conv RL-based Memory Agent | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k5nIOvYGCL\"},{\"title\":\"MemGPT: Towards LLMs as Operating Systems\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.08560\"},{\"title\":\"Cutting Through the Noise: Smarter Context Management for LLM-Powered Agents | The Research Blog\",\"url\":\"https://blog.jetbrains.com/research/2025/12/efficient-context-management/\"}]\n\nI've found several highly relevant results about LLM agent context compression, including multiple approaches and benchmarks:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n**MemGPT and Memory Management:**\nMemGPT proposes virtual context management, a technique drawing inspiration from hierarchical memory systems in traditional operating systems, introducing a system that intelligently manages different storage tiers to effectively provide extended context within the LLM's limited context window.\n\n**Context Compression Approaches:**\nMemGPT implements a virtual memory hierarchy inspired by operating systems, allowing LLMs to manage their own memory through explicit read/write operations. StreamingLLM addresses infinite context through attention sink tokens, but operates at the attention level rather than providing agent-level memory management.\n\n**ACON Framework (2025):**\nAgent Context Optimization (Acon) is a unified framework for systematic and adaptive context compression that dynamically condenses environment observations and interaction histories into concise, informative representations, using a guideline optimization pipeline that refines compressor prompts via failure analysis. ACON is validated on three multi-step agent benchmarks: AppWorld, OfficeBench, and Multi-objective QA, each requiring 15+ interaction steps.\n\n**Alternative Approaches:**\nMemAgent processes text in segments and updates memory through an overwrite strategy to address long-context tasks through enhanced memory management, extending the DAPO algorithm to directly optimize memory ability in an end-to-end fashion.\n\n**Recent Context Management Research:**\nThe two main approaches to context management are observation masking and LLM summarization.\n\nThe search results show that 2025 has seen active development in this area, with frameworks like ACON, MemAgent, and others providing baselines for evaluating agent context compression techniques.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"6c91499e-9f81-4af4-9cb5-e4d4a5fe0df0","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:03:43.656Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"LLM agent context compression sliding window MemGPT 2025 baselines AgentGym","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Ux69w42PDtzMuVoKTT9248","content":[{"title":"MemGPT","url":"https://research.memgpt.ai/"},{"title":"Active Context Compression: Autonomous Memory Management in LLM Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2601.07190"},{"title":"Scaling LLM Multi-turn RL with End-to-end Summarization- ...","url":"https://miaolu3.github.io/ArXiv_SUPO.pdf"},{"title":"Acon: Optimizing Context Compression for Long-horizon LLM Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2510.00615v1"},{"title":"Preprint MEMGPT: TOWARDS LLMS AS OPERATING SYSTEMS Charles Packer Vivian Fang","url":"https://readwise-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/media/wisereads/articles/memgpt-towards-llms-as-operati/MEMGPT.pdf"},{"title":"ACON: OPTIMIZING CONTEXT COMPRESSION FOR ...","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=7JbSwX6bNL"},{"title":"MemGPT: Towards LLMs as Operating Systems – Leonie Monigatti","url":"https://www.leoniemonigatti.com/papers/memgpt.html"},{"title":"MemAgent: Reshaping Long-Context LLM with Multi-Conv RL-based Memory Agent | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k5nIOvYGCL"},{"title":"MemGPT: Towards LLMs as Operating Systems","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.08560"},{"title":"Cutting Through the Noise: Smarter Context Management for LLM-Powered Agents | The Research Blog","url":"https://blog.jetbrains.com/research/2025/12/efficient-context-management/"}]},"I've found several highly relevant results about LLM agent context compression, including multiple approaches and benchmarks:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n**MemGPT and Memory Management:**\nMemGPT proposes virtual context management, a technique drawing inspiration from hierarchical memory systems in traditional operating systems, introducing a system that intelligently manages different storage tiers to effectively provide extended context within the LLM's limited context window.\n\n**Context Compression Approaches:**\nMemGPT implements a virtual memory hierarchy inspired by operating systems, allowing LLMs to manage their own memory through explicit read/write operations. StreamingLLM addresses infinite context through attention sink tokens, but operates at the attention level rather than providing agent-level memory management.\n\n**ACON Framework (2025):**\nAgent Context Optimization (Acon) is a unified framework for systematic and adaptive context compression that dynamically condenses environment observations and interaction histories into concise, informative representations, using a guideline optimization pipeline that refines compressor prompts via failure analysis. ACON is validated on three multi-step agent benchmarks: AppWorld, OfficeBench, and Multi-objective QA, each requiring 15+ interaction steps.\n\n**Alternative Approaches:**\nMemAgent processes text in segments and updates memory through an overwrite strategy to address long-context tasks through enhanced memory management, extending the DAPO algorithm to directly optimize memory ability in an end-to-end fashion.\n\n**Recent Context Management Research:**\nThe two main approaches to context management are observation masking and LLM summarization.\n\nThe search results show that 2025 has seen active development in this area, with frameworks like ACON, MemAgent, and others providing baselines for evaluating agent context compression techniques."],"durationSeconds":8.87309055600001}}
