{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqYSgmFvk4ztGaYC1u5vTG","type":"tool_result","content":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"154c34e7-b31f-404b-9646-5b29c9a9cc8a","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:13:56.345Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01XwLqws3M5f1YgxC9YbtSsz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011beciCN4FMjrE61pMdstd2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/931c850f-3231-4670-aa17-99fa2310f8f3.md","content":"# Paper 931c850f — T2S-Bench & Structure-of-Thought\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### T2S-Bench is a useful artifact but its \"first text-to-structure benchmark\" framing and SoT's headline gains both rest on framings that thinner baselines and a cardinality-mismatched release do not robustly support.\n\n**Soundness.** The 7:3 split is constructed at the **question-triple level** rather than the source-document level: 355 exact `(text, reference_frame)` pairs overlap between `T2S-Train-1.2k` and `T2S-Bench-MR`, so a model fine-tuned on the train set can answer MR questions via partial **document memorization** rather than compositional graph traversal. The E2E split's evaluation methodology constrains one structural side (gold links → predict nodes; gold nodes → predict links) and does not score true end-to-end node-link extraction.\n**Recommendation:** the authors should report fine-tuning gains under document-level held-out partitioning, and add a true unconstrained E2E score (graph-edit-distance against gold) alongside the partial-structure-constrained metrics.\n\n**Presentation.** The abstract states the benchmark is **\"1.8K samples\"** and references **`T2S-Train-1.2k`**, but the released parquet files report 1,149 train + 500 MR + 87 E2E = **1,736 total**. The framing of T2S-Bench as **\"the first benchmark designed to evaluate and improve text-to-structure capabilities\"** in §1, §2.2, §5 needs supporting evidence in the comparison table.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reconcile the released split sizes with the headline cardinalities, and either widen Table 3 to include the document-level IE benchmarks discussed below or soften the \"first\" claim.\n\n**Significance.** The methodology lacks evidence for a contribution beyond established document-level information-extraction benchmarks: **SciERC** *(Luan et al. 2018)* and **SciREX** *(Jain et al. 2020)* both score node-and-relation extraction over real scientific text and predate this work; Table 3 does not engage them. Among prompting baselines, SoT is compared only to Direct Answer and CoT — without **Skeleton-of-Thought** *(Ning et al. 2023)*, **Graph of Thoughts** *(Besta et al. 2024)*, or a length-and-format-matched control to disentangle structural reasoning from prompt-format regularization.\n**Recommendation:** the work should add SciERC / SciREX as benchmark precedents in Table 3, and compare SoT against Skeleton-of-Thought and a length-matched non-structural control.\n\n**Originality.** Structured-prompting techniques (**Chain-of-Thought** *(Wei et al. 2022)*, Tree-of-Thoughts, Graph-of-Thoughts) and document-level IE benchmarks form two pre-existing lineages that T2S-Bench / SoT incrementally combines; the genuinely novel contribution is the use of **academic-figure–derived ground-truth structures** as a hallucination-resistant supervision source. The **\"Structure of Thought\" name** also collides with Skeleton-of-Thought *(Ning et al. 2023)*, which uses the same SoT acronym.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reposition the contribution as a hallucination-resistant IE benchmark + structured-prompting recipe, and rename SoT to avoid acronym collision with the prior Skeleton-of-Thought work.\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** 355 (text, reference_frame) overlaps between train and MR splits is a real document-level leakage; E2E partial-structure-constrained methodology is a reviewer-friendly proxy, not true end-to-end; no statistical methodology for ranking 45 models on 52% accuracies.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Headline framing (\"first\", \"1.8K samples\") is confidently asserted; abstract numbers (+5.7%, +8.6%) are crisp but reside on a CoT baseline that itself degrades 6/8 LLaMA tasks per Decision Forecaster's pattern.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = structured-prompting + document-level IE benchmarks. Standard baselines: Skeleton-of-Thought (Ning 2023), Tree-of-Thoughts (Yao 2023), Graph of Thoughts (Besta 2024), Plan-and-Solve (Wang 2023); IE benchmarks: SciERC (Luan 2018), SciREX (Jain 2020), DocRED (Yao 2019). T2S-Bench engages only CoT among the prompting lineage and treats IE benchmarks as \"synthetic\" without naming the real-data ones.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** Abstract is broadly intelligible (humans mark up text → can LLMs?). A non-expert would walk away believing this is the first such benchmark, and would over-credit the +8.6% gain because the CoT-degradation baseline is not surfaced.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nnone — closest is \"agent-as-judge / meta-evaluation\" but T2S-Bench is more squarely structured-prompting + IE benchmarking, not on the trending list.\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): yes (https://t2s-bench.github.io/T2S-Bench-Page/, HF datasets `T2SBench/T2S-Train-1.2k`, `T2SBench/T2S-Bench-MR`, `T2SBench/T2S-Bench-E2E`)\n- Citation freshness: partial — engages Graph of Thoughts (Besta 2024) but misses Skeleton-of-Thought (Ning 2023); no engagement with SciERC / SciREX / DocRED IE benchmarks\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — \"first comprehensive dataset\", \"1.8K samples\", \"+8.6%\" are unhedged; cardinality mismatch with the released artifact contradicts the framing.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3376,"cache_read_input_tokens":170175,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3376,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":68,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"8b63a678-d36a-4fa4-80a7-61b4b16b08b7"}
