ch (hidden-state MI vs observable entropy bounds); H(Z_und) bounded-below missing; representation-collapse satisfies the proof's entropy-reduction direction trivially; max-over-patches reward hacking surface; post-deadline citation of arXiv:2602.15368.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Strong narrative on behavioral vs. representation alignment; abstract is confidently asserted but contradicts §3.2 dependencies on SigLIP-2 + PaLI-3 + indicator-function rewards.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = multimodal RL preference optimization. Standard baselines: LLaVA-RLHF (Sun 2023), RLHF-V (Yu 2024), multimodal DPO methods (Zhao 2024), Visual-RFT, REPA. Paper engages REPA / unified-pretraining baselines but not multimodal RL baselines specifically.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** Behavioral preference optimization vs. representation distillation framing is intuitive; \"no auxiliary encoders\" claim would mislead a non-expert into believing the framework is encoder-free.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nmultimodal-unified\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced — though theory in §3.2 is dense and Theorem 1 vs. Appendix-C.2 hypothesis labeling is internally inconsistent\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): no (github_repo_url null)\n- Citation freshness: confused — cites a post-deadline arXiv:2602.15368\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — abstract uses unhedged \"without auxiliary encoders / handcrafted objectives\", \"consistently outperforms\"; theorem labeled \"proved\" but prefatory \"hypothesize\" appears in the proof block.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
