{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0163sY4ZoRVeqK3quXbCq17L","type":"tool_result","content":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"935af0ea-a275-4723-9227-ceb1fba6c63b","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:20:13.406Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Rwpf3ny9G3th5NBDpeDPPU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018HVSUpsuXQ17U4AYcBLP7J","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/ef666d10-db2a-456f-a5c4-33d0c0717a77.md","content":"# Paper ef666d10 — SpatialAnt: Autonomous Zero-Shot Robot Navigation via Active Scene Reconstruction and Visual Anticipation\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### SpatialAnt's autonomous pre-exploration + visual-anticipation framing is a genuine sim-to-real contribution, but the headline 66 / 50.8 / 52 SR numbers rest on subsampled splits and a private 25-path real-world benchmark with no released artifacts.\n\n**Soundness.** §3 specifies the **metric-alignment factor** as the \"average ratio over valid pixels\" while the displayed equation is an unnormalized sum, leaving the load-bearing **monocular metric-scale recovery** step ambiguous between two implementations. The Section 4 evaluation uses subsampled val-unseen splits (100 episodes for R2R-CE, 195 for RxR-CE) without released sample manifests, seeds, or logs. The Table 3 column-0 percentage breakdown sums to 16% rather than 100%, suggesting a typesetting or missing-category error.\n**Recommendation:** the authors should reconcile the §3 equation with the \"average ratio\" description, release the sampled R2R-CE / RxR-CE episode manifests + seeds, and audit Table 3 for the percentage-sum anomaly.\n\n**Presentation.** The abstract foregrounds three numbers — **\"66% SR on R2R-CE\"**, **\"50.8% SR on RxR-CE\"**, and **\"52% SR in challenging real-world settings\"** — without surfacing that the simulation results are on subsampled subsets and the real-world result is on a private 25-path benchmark. Reproducibility-relevant artifacts (episode lists, Hello Robot paths, reconstruction logs) are not currently linked.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reframe abstract numbers as \"subsampled subset\" + \"private 25-path Hello Robot benchmark\" with explicit sample sizes, and release the supporting artifacts before deliberation closes.\n\n**Significance.** The methodology lacks evidence for SoTA over the modern zero-shot VLN frontier: standard baselines such as **NavGPT** *(Zhou et al. 2023)*, **MapGPT** *(Chen et al. 2024)*, and **NaVid** *(Zhang et al. 2024)* are not engaged. The Hello-Robot deployment is impressive but a 25-path benchmark cannot stand in for cross-environment generalization claims.\n**Recommendation:** the work should add NavGPT, MapGPT, and NaVid as zero-shot VLN baselines on the full R2R-CE / RxR-CE val-unseen splits, and expand the real-world deployment benchmark beyond 25 paths.\n\n**Originality.** The pipeline composes established components (**SLAM3R** *(Liu et al. 2024)* reconstruction, **Depth-Anything-2** monocular depth, **Gaussian-Splatting**-based novel-view rendering, frontier-based DFS exploration, set-cover / 2-opt planning); the **visual-anticipation mechanism** that uses noisy point clouds to render future observations for counterfactual sub-path pruning is the genuinely novel contribution. The contribution is one of integration rather than a new fundamental method.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reposition the contribution as a sim-to-real integration pipeline whose novelty is the visual-anticipation mechanism, and ablate it against simpler view-prediction baselines (e.g., raw point-cloud rendering without GS).\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** §3 metric-alignment notation/equation mismatch; subsampled R2R-CE/RxR-CE evaluation not the full val-unseen split; private 25-path Hello Robot benchmark; Table 3 column-0 sums to 16%; no public artifact.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Strong narrative on bridging sim-to-real gap; abstract is confidently asserted with three crisp SR numbers; reader has to dig into §4 to see the subsampling.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = zero-shot VLN. Standard 2023–2024 baselines: NavGPT (Zhou 2023), MapGPT (Chen 2024), NaVid (Zhang 2024), CO-LLM, A2Nav, BEVBert. Paper engages SpatialNav primarily; the broader zero-shot VLN frontier is unaddressed.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** Robot-friendly framing (autonomous pre-exploration + counterfactual reasoning) is intuitive; a non-expert would credit the 66% / 50.8% / 52% SR numbers as full-benchmark results.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nworld-models — embodied VLN with anticipated-observation rendering qualifies under \"world models, embodied AI, robotic policy\"\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): no (github_urls=[])\n- Citation freshness: partial — engages SpatialNav and SLAM3R / Depth-Anything-2; missing NavGPT / MapGPT / NaVid baselines\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — abstract uses unhedged \"significantly outperforms\", \"66%\", \"50.8%\", \"52%\"; subsampling and private-benchmark caveats not surfaced.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2403,"cache_read_input_tokens":242241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2403,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":71,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"6e63ea1e-7acf-4846-b44f-e72695735f6e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018HVSUpsuXQ17U4AYcBLP7J","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/ef666d10-db2a-456f-a5c4-33d0c0717a77.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"3a6dd1de-a771-4955-ae9d-8eca1588083b","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:20:35.943Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/ef666d10-db2a-456f-a5c4-33d0c0717a77.md","content":"# Paper ef666d10 — SpatialAnt: Autonomous Zero-Shot Robot Navigation via Active Scene Reconstruction and Visual Anticipation\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### SpatialAnt's autonomous pre-exploration + visual-anticipation framing is a genuine sim-to-real contribution, but the headline 66 / 50.8 / 52 SR numbers rest on subsampled splits and a private 25-path real-world benchmark with no released artifacts.\n\n**Soundness.** §3 specifies the **metric-alignment factor** as the \"average ratio over valid pixels\" while the displayed equation is an unnormalized sum, leaving the load-bearing **monocular metric-scale recovery** step ambiguous between two implementations. The Section 4 evaluation uses subsampled val-unseen splits (100 episodes for R2R-CE, 195 for RxR-CE) without released sample manifests, seeds, or logs. The Table 3 column-0 percentage breakdown sums to 16% rather than 100%, suggesting a typesetting or missing-category error.\n**Recommendation:** the authors should reconcile the §3 equation with the \"average ratio\" description, release the sampled R2R-CE / RxR-CE episode manifests + seeds, and audit Table 3 for the percentage-sum anomaly.\n\n**Presentation.** The abstract foregrounds three numbers — **\"66% SR on R2R-CE\"**, **\"50.8% SR on RxR-CE\"**, and **\"52% SR in challenging real-world settings\"** — without surfacing that the simulation results are on subsampled subsets and the real-world result is on a private 25-path benchmark. Reproducibility-relevant artifacts (episode lists, Hello Robot paths, reconstruction logs) are not currently linked.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reframe abstract numbers as \"subsampled subset\" + \"private 25-path Hello Robot benchmark\" with explicit sample sizes, and release the supporting artifacts before deliberation closes.\n\n**Significance.** The methodology lacks evidence for SoTA over the modern zero-shot VLN frontier: standard baselines such as **NavGPT** *(Zhou et al. 2023)*, **MapGPT** *(Chen et al. 2024)*, and **NaVid** *(Zhang et al. 2024)* are not engaged. The Hello-Robot deployment is impressive but a 25-path benchmark cannot stand in for cross-environment generalization claims.\n**Recommendation:** the work should add NavGPT, MapGPT, and NaVid as zero-shot VLN baselines on the full R2R-CE / RxR-CE val-unseen splits, and expand the real-world deployment benchmark beyond 25 paths.\n\n**Originality.** The pipeline composes established components (**SLAM3R** *(Liu et al. 2024)* reconstruction, **Depth-Anything-2** monocular depth, **Gaussian-Splatting**-based novel-view rendering, frontier-based DFS exploration, set-cover / 2-opt planning); the **visual-anticipation mechanism** that uses noisy point clouds to render future observations for counterfactual sub-path pruning is the genuinely novel contribution. The contribution is one of integration rather than a new fundamental method.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reposition the contribution as a sim-to-real integration pipeline whose novelty is the visual-anticipation mechanism, and ablate it against simpler view-prediction baselines (e.g., raw point-cloud rendering without GS).\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** §3 metric-alignment notation/equation mismatch; subsampled R2R-CE/RxR-CE evaluation not the full val-unseen split; private 25-path Hello Robot benchmark; Table 3 column-0 sums to 16%; no public artifact.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Strong narrative on bridging sim-to-real gap; abstract is confidently asserted with three crisp SR numbers; reader has to dig into §4 to see the subsampling.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = zero-shot VLN. Standard 2023–2024 baselines: NavGPT (Zhou 2023), MapGPT (Chen 2024), NaVid (Zhang 2024), CO-LLM, A2Nav, BEVBert. Paper engages SpatialNav primarily; the broader zero-shot VLN frontier is unaddressed.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** Robot-friendly framing (autonomous pre-exploration + counterfactual reasoning) is intuitive; a non-expert would credit the 66% / 50.8% / 52% SR numbers as full-benchmark results.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nworld-models — embodied VLN with anticipated-observation rendering qualifies under \"world models, embodied AI, robotic policy\"\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): no (github_urls=[])\n- Citation freshness: partial — engages SpatialNav and SLAM3R / Depth-Anything-2; missing NavGPT / MapGPT / NaVid baselines\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — abstract uses unhedged \"significantly outperforms\", \"66%\", \"50.8%\", \"52%\"; subsampling and private-benchmark caveats not surfaced.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
